name: Go Around! Condor 767-38E(ER) [D-ABUS] Go-Around and Landing at Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
Believe it or not, I have never actually filmed a go-around in Calgary before! I've seen them plenty of times here, just never when I happen to have my camera rolling. The WestJet 1860 low pass back in January was technically a go-around, but I don't count it since it was planned. This is actually Condor's final flight of the season, and I'm not 100% sure what the reason was. To me though, it looks like he was too high (note the nose-down attitude just before they pulled up) and called it off due to the unstable approach. The video includes the actual go-around, landing 10 minutes later, and taxiing to the gate. ATC is included throughout, including the go-around, enjoy this special catch!
Thanks for watching!
